'm%20a%20softie%20deep%20down.%20Disciplining%20my%20children%20is%20hard.%20In%20those%20moments%2C%20I%20remind%20myself%20they'll%20achieve%20greater%20things%20because%20they%20developed%20core%20values%20and%20an%20understanding%20of%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20channel%20both%20of%20our%20approaches%20through%20disciplinarian%20actions%20and%20kindness.%20This%20gives%20our%20parenting%20a%20higher%20purpose%20than%20just%20trying%20to%20keep%20the%20peace%20to%20get%20through%20the%20day%20as%20a%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20thought%20about%20how%20I%20would%20parent%20my%20kids%20for%20decades.%20Even%20as%20a%20teenager%2C%20I%20saw%20how%20important%20it%20was%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC10106685%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egive%20attention%20to%20your%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20my%20parents%20didn't%20always%20have%20the%20time%20to%20do%20so.%20And%20for%20good%20reason%20%E2%80%94%20they%20rarely%20had%20a%20moment%20to%20rest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fa11cde4-27f7-4e54-b4fe-887396cac92a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20our%20parenting%20style%20looks%20like%20in%20action%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20keep%20these%20values%20in%20mind%20during%20moments%20like%20yesterday.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20had%20to%20enforce%20our%20authoritarian%20parenting%20style%20in%20the%20grocery%20store%2C%20even%20though%20we%20were%20rushing%20to%20get%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%205-year-old%20son%20grabbed%20a%20box%20of%20mac%20and%20cheese%20off%20the%20shelf%20and%20threw%20it%20in%20our%20cart.%20While%20I%20put%20the%20box%20back%2C%20my%20husband%20told%20him%20it%20wasn't%20on%20our%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20son%20immediately%20started%20crying%20and%20yelling.%20He%20said%20we%20were%20mean%2C%20which%20I%20shut%20down%20right%20away.%20I%20told%20him%20he%20couldn't%20speak%20to%20us%20like%20that%20because%20he%20needed%20to%20respect%20us%2C%20and%20if%20he%20said%20it%20again%2C%20he'd%20lose%20TV%20privileges%20after%20dinner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crying%20continued%20as%20we%20walked%20down%20other%20aisles.%20When%20my%20husband%20shushed%20our%20son%2C%20he%20repeated%20that%20we%20were%20mean.%20When%20we%20got%20home%2C%20we%20stuck%20to%20our%20word%2C%20and%20he%20didn't%20get%20to%20watch%20%26quot%3BPaw%20Patrol.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20would%20have%20tried%20to%20quiet%20him%20in%20the%20store%20and%20eventually%20given%20up.%20Instead%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20explained%20why%20our%20son's%20language%20was%20wrong%20before%20enforcing%20the%20promised%20consequence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20our%20son%20pouted%20in%20his%20room%20later%20that%20night%2C%20we%20talked%20about%20why%20respecting%20us%20was%20important%2C%20how%20much%20we%20loved%20him%2C%20and%20how%20he%20should%20apologize.%20I%20know%20he'll%20learn%20over%20time%20that%20he%20can't%20do%20whatever%20he%20wants%2C%20which%20will%20make%20him%20a%20happier%20adult%20who%20people%20love%20to%20be%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20we%20also%20discussed%20how%20our%20actions%20have%20consequences%20with%20our%208-year-old%20daughter.%20She%20wanted%20to%20ride%20her%20bike%20to%20a%20friend's%20house%20after%20dinner%2C%20but%20it%20was%20too%20late%20on%20a%20school%20night.%20My%20husband%20said%20no%2C%20and%20our%20daughter%20rolled%20her%20eyes%20and%20ran%20to%20her%20room%2C%20slamming%20the%20door%20behind%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20immediately%20went%20to%20her%20room%20and%20told%20her%20we%20don't%20do%20either%20of%20those%20things%20because%20they're%20disrespectful.%20She%20needed%20to%20apologize%20and%20accept%20her%20punishment%20%E2%80%94%20no%20bike%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20old%20enough%20to%20see%20how%20other%20parents%20treat%20their%20kids%2C%20so%20she%20pointed%20out%20how%20her%20best%20friend%20slams%20the%20door%20and%20never%20gets%20punished.%20She%20thought%20it%20was%20unfair%20that%20other%20kids%20could%20express%20their%20anger%20without%20punishment%20while%20she%20couldn't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20told%20her%20she%20was%20allowed%20to%20feel%20mad.%20He%20also%20explained%20she%20should%20tell%20us%20about%20her%20feelings%20with%20words%20so%20we%20could%20work%20through%20them%20together%2C%20and%20said%20that%20would%20be%20more%20helpful%20than%20slamming%20doors%20or%20rolling%20her%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20made%20a%20great%20point%20by%20asking%20how%20our%20daughter%20felt%20when%20her%20best%20friend%20rolled%20her%20eyes%20at%20her.%20My%208-year-old%20said%20it%20was%20annoying.%20I%20saw%20her%20realize%20in%20real%20time%20that%20it%20wasn't%20as%20helpful%20as%20talking%20through%20her%20feelings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20need%20to%20take%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fparenting%2Fauthoritarian-parenting%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20loving%20approach%20to%20discipline%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20do%20so%20by%20discussing%20why%20their%20consequences%20happen%20and%20how%20much%20we%20love%20our%20kids%20no%20matter%20what.%20I%20believe%20that%20our%20kids%20benefit%20from%20my%20slightly%20emotionally%20detached%2C%20logical%20approach%20and%20my%20husband's%20strength%20in%20emotional%20vulnerability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEnforcing%20rules%20sometimes%20makes%20me%20feel%20like%20a%20bad%20mom%2C%20but%20those%20moments%20when%20I%20see%20the%20lightbulb%20spark%20in%20my%20children's%20minds%20are%20worth%20it.%20When%20I%20doubt%20myself%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-right-way-to-set-boundaries-with-people-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhile%20setting%20boundaries%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20making%20disciplinary%20decisions%2C%20I%20remember%20that%20we're%20preparing%20them%20to%20be%20well-rounded%20adults.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20kids%20are%20incredible%20now%2C%20and%20they'll%20be%