k-q1-result-net-profit-up-35-at-rs-16-175-cr-nii-at-rs-29-837-cr-124072000427_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fhdfc-bank-q1-result-net-profit-up-35-at-rs-16-175-cr-nii-at-rs-29-837-cr-124072000427_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nearly%201%2C000%20Indian%20Students%20Return%20From%20Bangladesh%2C%204%2C000%20Still%20Remain%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20civil%20unrest%20in%20Bangladesh%20continues%2C%20the%20Indian%20High%20Commission%20in%20Dhaka%20is%20facilitating%20safe%20travel%20for%20Indian%20students%20to%20crossing%20points%20along%20the%20India-Bangladesh%20International%20Border.%20The%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20(MEA)%20is%20also%20collaborating%20with%20civil%20aviation%2C%20immigration%2C%20land%20ports%2C%20and%20the%20Border%20Security%20Force%20(BSF)%20to%20ensure%20a%20smooth%20passage%20for%20Indian%20nationals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20778%20Indian%20students%20have%20successfully%20returned%20to%20India%20via%20various%20land%20ports.%20Additionally%2C%20around%20200%20students%20have%20returned%20home%20by%20regular%20flight%20services%20through%20Dhaka%20and%20Chittagong%20airports%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37982%2FUpdate_on_Return_of_Indian_Nationals_in_Bangladesh%5C%22%3Ethe%20MEA%20said%20in%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20High%20Commission%20is%20in%20regular%20contact%20with%20more%20than%204%2C000%20students%20still%20in%20various%20universities%20across%20Bangladesh.%20Students%20from%20Nepal%20and%20Bhutan%20have%20also%20been%20aided%20in%20crossing%20into%20India%20upon%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20students%20had%20booked%20air%20tickets.%20But%20since%20there%20is%20a%20curfew%20in%20place%2C%20they%20could%20not%20make%20it%20to%20the%20airport.%20Several%20flights%20were%20also%20cancelled.%20There%20are%20still%20many%20Indian%20students%20still%20in%20hostels%20at%20universities%20where%20the%20atmosphere%20is%20still%20peaceful%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20Indian%20student%20who%20returned%20from%20Bangladesh%20told%20NDTV.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20High%20Commission%20in%20Dhaka%20is%20also%20coordinating%20with%20Bangladesh's%20civil%20aviation%20authorities%20and%20commercial%20airlines%20to%20ensure%20uninterrupted%20flight%20services%20to%20India%20from%20Dhaka%20and%20Chittagong%2C%20which%20can%20be%20used%20by%20Indian%20nationals%20to%20return%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20Happening%20In%20Bangladesh%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh%20has%20plunged%20into%20turmoil%20this%20week%20as%20clashes%20between%20student%20protesters%2C%20security%20officials%2C%20and%20pro-government%20student%20activists%20erupted%20over%20a%20contentious%20quota%20system%20for%20government%20jobs.%20The%20escalating%20violence%20has%20prompted%20protest%20organizers%20to%20call%20for%20a%20nationwide%20shutdown%2C%20with%20universities%20across%20the%20country%20closing%20their%20doors%20indefinitely%20in%20response%20to%20the%20unrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fg3hoga28_bangladesh-protests-reuters-_625x300_20_July_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Reuters%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20protests%2C%20which%20began%20late%20last%20month%2C%20reached%20a%20boiling%20point%20on%20Monday%20when%20student%20activists%20at%20Dhaka%20University%2C%20the%20largest%20university%20in%20the%20country%2C%20engaged%20in%20violent%20clashes%20with%20police%20and%20counter-protesters%20aligned%20with%20the%20ruling%20Awami%20League.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20quota%20reserves%20up%20to%2030%20per%20cent%20of%20government%20jobs%20for%20family%20members%20of%20veterans%20who%20fought%20in%20Bangladesh's%201971%20war%20of%20independence%20against%20Pakistan.%20Protesters%20argue%20that%20this%20system%20is%20discriminatory%20and%20disproportionately%20benefits%20supporters%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20Awami%20League%20party.%20They%20advocate%20for%20a%20merit-based%20system%20to%20replace%20the%20existing%20quota.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EProtests%20Intensify%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20in%20the%20country%20has%20escalated%2C%20with%20soldiers%20patrolling%20cities%20to%20quell%20the%20civil%20unrest.%20Riot%20police%20have%20fired%20on%20protesters%20who%20defied%20a%20government-imposed%20curfew%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20volatile%20and%20dangerous%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20week's%20violence%20has%20resulted%20in%20at%20least%20115%20deaths%2C%20posing%20a%20monumental%20challenge%20to%20PM%20Hasina's%20government.%20The%20curfew%2C%20which%20went%20into%20effect%20at%20midnight%2C%20was%20accompanied%20by%20a%20request%20from%20the%20PM%20Hasina's%20office%20for%20military%20deployment%20after%20police%20failed%20to%20subdue%20widespread%20disorder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20army%20has%20been%20deployed%20nationwide%20to%20control%20the%20law%20and%20order%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20Bangladesh%20armed%20forces%20spokesperson%20Shahdat%20Hossain%20told%20news%20agency%20AFP.%20The%20curfew%20will%20remain%20in%20effect%20until%20at%20least%2010%3A00%20am%20on%20Sunday%2C%20according%20to%20local%20media.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721469180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fv0ne6s1g_indian-students-bangladesh-ani_625x300_20_July_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbangladesh-protests-nearly-1-000-indians-return-from-violence-hit-bangladesh-4-000-still-remain-6147446%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20the%20civil%20unrest%20in%20Bangladesh%20continues%2C%2